DPRK on 4th DPRK-U.S. missile negotiations
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The spokesman for the Foreign Ministry of the DPRK gave an answer to a question put by KCNA today as regards the DPRK-U.S. missile negotiations held in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He said:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The 4th round of DPRK-U.S. missile negotiations was held in Pyongyang on March 29 and 30.   At the negotiations, we said our consistent stand is that we will never bargain with anyone about our development, production, test and deployment of missiles because this belongs to our sovereignty from A to Z.  We reclarified our stand that we might discuss the issue of suspending the export of our missiles if the U.S. side wants, provided that it makes a cash compensation for our foreign currency losses to be entailed by our suspension of missile exports. In this connection, we put forward a proposal on cash compensation for the suspension of missile exports.   Therefore, the negotiations discussed our proposal and agreed to continue the discussion in the future, too.   It was agreed that the venue and date for next negotiations would be confirmed through a contact channel in New York.

President Kim Il Sung is eternal sun of Juche
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The President Kim Il Sung was the father of the nation who saved the destiny of the country and the nation for the Korean people and brought the greatest progress and prosperity to this land, founder of socialist Korea and sun of humankind who brightly indicated the road for the world people to follow, said M. D. Salim, deputy speaker of Rajya Sabha (Upper House) of India, when interviewed by  KCNA in his country on March 25 on the occasion of Sun's Day (April 15).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people are revering the respected President Kim Il Sung as a peerlessly great man and the eternal sun of Juche whom they acclaimed for the first time in their history spanning thousands of years, he said, and went on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The President made all efforts to reunify the country from the very day when the country was divided by outside forces.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The President put forward the unique three principles of national reunification, the proposal on founding the Democratic Confederal Republic of Koryo and the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation, which reflected the strong ideas of independence and patriotism on the basis of the Juche idea.   Nothing is better than this proposal as far as the way of independent and peaceful reunification of Korea is concerned.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   M. M. Verma, director of the Indian Center for UN Studies, in a statement issued on the occasion of Sun's Day  said that hundreds of millions of people of the world are highly praising the great leader Kim Il Sung as the sun of independence and sun of Juche.

Struggle for right to existence supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- Workers, farmers and fishermen in South Korea are holding large-scale anti-"government" rallies and demonstrations in all parts of it to demand a stop to the "unilateral restructuring", urge the implementation of the "agricultural policy commitment", attain the right to existence and frustrate the sycophantic treacherous moves of the authorities.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun today says their massive struggle is an eruption of curse and wrath upon the rulers who are imposing utter political non-right, abject poverty, unbearable sufferings and sacrifices upon them.   The news analyst goes on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Over the last one year since his coming to power, the chief executive of South Korea has left the economy as a whole to the tender mercy of the U.S. and other outsiders, rendering a large number of people unemployed, and sold off Tok Islet and fishing grounds around it to the Japanese reactionaries, the sworn enemy of the Korean nation, through the signing of the treacherous "fishery accord", thus leaving millions of workers and more than 500,000 fishermen jobless.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The fact clearly shows the working people can never get rid of miserable plight and death unless they smash the colonial economic trusteeship of the U.S. over South Korea, the sycophantic treacheries of the South Korean rulers and their anti-social misrule.
   It is only too natural and just for them to have risen in this massive struggle.

DPRK exposes nature of planned U.S. "NMD" system 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The spokesman for the Foreign Ministry of the DPRK gave an answer to a question put by KCNA today as regards the "National Missile Defense (NMD)" system which is being pushed by the United States in real earnest these days under the pretext of threats from the DPRK.   As was reported, the U.S. senate and the house of representatives adopted a bill on taking the development of the "NMD" system as an official national policy of the United States on March 17 and 18 on the plea of "protecting the U.S. from missile attacks."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The United States is now vociferating about "missile threat" from the DPRK and other countries as if it were imminent. But, the U.S. projected "NMD" system is, in essence, a replica of the "star wars" program to militarily contain other big powers and attain its ambition for world supremacy.   Nevertheless, the U.S. is now finding faults with the missile activities in the DPRK. Their allegation is nothing but a groundless pretext.   It is the DPRK's legitimate right of self defence to develop, test and produce missiles by its own efforts to defend the security of the country because the U.S. is posing constant threats to it with enormous nuclear missiles and weapons of mass destruction.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   No matter how zealously the U.S. may talk about "threat" of the DPRK's missiles,  it cannot justify its arms buildup.   Instead of adopting a dangerous bill which will touch off a new arms race and Cold War by filling pockets of  munitions monopolies and posing direct threats to neighboring big powers, the U.S. congress must above all solve the issue of completely and comprehensively eliminating all weapons of mass destruction including nuclear weapons.
